provenance: Percy's last-ditch effort appeared to have paid off, as he was able to edge out Seith to win what would end up being his third and final term in the Senate.Amherst ( ) is a town in Hampshire County, Massachusetts, United States, in the Connecticut River valley.
The town is home to Amherst College, Hampshire College, and the University of Massachusetts Amherst, three of the Five Colleges.

The name of the town is pronounced without the "h" ("AM-erst"), giving rise to the local saying, "only the 'h' is silent", in reference both to the pronunciation and to the town's politically active populace.
